  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper, we prove the Frankel's refinement of Bochner's theorem on both compact and forward complete Finsler manifolds. That is, on a compact or forward complete Finsler manifold <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math> with non-positive flag curvature and negative (mean) Ricci curvature, any isometry <math altimg="si125.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>ψ</mi><mo>:</mo><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">→</mo><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math> homotopic to the identity must be the identity itself.</subfield>
